{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"10104","heading":"Recruitment bonuses","label":"10104 Recruitment bonuses","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/ptIII/sptI/ch101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of this chapter, referred to in subsec. (e), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 109–295Oct. 4, 2006"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—In General","label":"a .—In General","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Administrator may pay a bonus to an individual in order to recruit the individual for a position within the Agency that would otherwise be difficult to fill in the absence of such a bonus. Upon completion of the strategic human capital plan, such bonuses shall be paid in accordance with that plan.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Bonus Amount.—","label":"b Bonus Amount.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The amount of a bonus under this section shall be determined by the Administrator, but may not exceed 25 percent of the annual rate of basic pay of the position involved.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":".—Form of payment","label":"2 .—Form of payment","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A bonus under this section shall be paid in the form of a lump-sum payment and shall not be considered to be part of basic pay.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Service Agreements","label":"c .—Service Agreements","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the period of service the individual shall be required to complete in return for the bonus; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the conditions under which the agreement may be terminated before the agreed-upon service period has been completed, and the effect of the termination.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Eligibility","label":"d .—Eligibility","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a position to which an individual is appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a position in the Senior Executive Service as a noncareer appointee (as defined in section 3132(a)); or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a position which has been excepted from the competitive service by reason of its confidential, policy-determining, policy-making, or policy-advocating character.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Termination","label":"e .—Termination","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The authority to pay bonuses under this section shall terminate 5 years after the date of enactment of this chapter.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Reports.—","label":"f Reports.—","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":".—In general","label":"1 .—In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Agency shall submit to the appropriate committees of Congress, annually for each of the 5 years during which this section is in effect, a report on the operation of this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":".—Contents","label":"2 .—Contents","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Ff%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the number and dollar amount of bonuses paid to individuals holding positions within each pay grade, pay level, or other pay classification; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t5/s10104/f/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft5%2Fs10104%2Ff%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a determination of the extent to which such bonuses furthered the purposes of this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}
